s from 150kg and up to 300kg to create a sense of safety for you during work at a certain height.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://salt.tikicdn.com/ts/tmp/9b/eb/bb/774b1b78def015878c1979a6714a59f2.jpg\" style=\"border-style:none; height:750px; width:750px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Instructions on how to use the cheap aluminum escalator SK 380 properly.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 1: How to extend the ladder</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Remove the forming pin of the ladder</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Next:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Place ladders on straight surfaces</li>\r\n	<li>Place your feet on the bottom stairs to hold the ladder fixed before climbing high</li>\r\n	<li>Use 2 hands to pull the hook of the 3rd bar from the bottom up</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure each step has been towed to the maximum and securely locked</li>\r\n	<li>Depending on the height you want to fit the job, drag the number of steps.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 2: How to fold the ladder</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hold the ladder with the hooks under the ladder bar where you are opening the latch</li>\r\n	<li>Place 2 thumbs on the latch you are about to remove</li>\r\n	<li>Place your remaining fingers under the hook (if you place above the hook you may be sandwiched between the bars)</li>\r\n	<li>At the same time, close the latch at the same time until the front bar pulls down</li>\r\n	<li>Repeat it like that with the rest of the steps.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 3: Close the ladder</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To make sure the ladder has been tightly closed and ensure user safety should check the ladder positioning latch.</li>\r\n	<li>Absolutely do not pull the ladder with the bar because the ladder can be opened and cause injury to the user as well as the ladder will quickly break down.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>* Specifications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>SUMIKA<br />\r\nShortened Aluminum Ladder Model:<br />\r\nSK380 - Dimens