       (100042, 100001, 'My Sweet Orange Tree',
        ',https://salt.tikicdn.com/cache/w444/ts/product/5e/18/24/2a6154ba08df6ce6161c13f4303fa19e.jpg', 78900, 300,
        '<p>&quot;The sourness of poverty blends with the sweetness of discovering what makes this life worthy of a Brazilian classic.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Booklist</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;A way of seeing life almost completely from the eyes of children ... has the power to warm and break the heart, no matter what age the reader is.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- The National.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get acquainted with Zez&eacute;, the super mischievous boy who is also the most adorable, with the dream of growing up to be a butterfly-necked poet. Not everyone admits that &quot;lovely&quot; amount. Because, in that poor suburban neighborhood, austerity has blinded people&#39;s eyes to the honest heart and wonderful imagination of the five-year-old boy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is nothing much to sneeze, scold, because Zez&eacute; had a special friend to vent his heart: the sweet orange tree in the back garden. And a friend, in the flesh, one day appeared, to the sensitive boy soon to know what was affectionate, what was pain, and forever changed his life.<br />\r\nOpening with clear sounds and ending in nostalgic notes, my Sweet Orange Tree makes us realize the true beauty of life comes from simple things like the white flower of the back tree, and that life is miserable without love and compassion. This classic book has therefore constantly awakened the hearts of readers around the world, since its debut in 1968 in Brazil.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>author:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>JOS&Eacute; MAURO DE VASCONCELOS (1920&ndash;1984) was a Brazilian writer. Born into a poor family on the outskirts of Rio de Janeiro, growing up he had to do enough work to make a living. But with his natural storytelling talent, extraordinary memory, great imagination and abundant living capital, Jos&eacute; felt in himself the urge to become a writer and began writing at the age of 22. His most famous work is my autobiographical novel Sweet Orange Tree. The book was included in Brazil&#39;s primary school program, which was sold to twenty countries and adapted into a film. In addition, Jos&eacute; was very successful as a film actor and screenwriter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Product prices on Tiki are inclusive of taxes under applicable law. However, depending on the type of product or method, delivery address, additional costs such as shipping fees, bulky cargo surcharges, ...</p>\r\n',
