        174600, 200,
        '<p>&lt;iframe width=&quot;880&quot; height=&quot;421&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/qquL_0vthcY&quot; title=&quot;YouTube video player&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The BlueBird Flies Home</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike previous works set in the central countryside full of nostalgic childhood, clear with characters in puberty, in this new book writer Nguyen Nhat Anh is set in Saigon &ndash; Ho Chi Minh City where the author lives (as a gratitude to the land of the South). The main characters in the story are also &quot;bigger&quot;, with the stories of a very challenging career of ambitious young students. Of course, it is indispensable for emotional, dramatic and unexpected stories that make readers look away, laugh out of tears. And as in all Nguyen Nhat Anh works, kind and spirituality are still important highlights in this new book.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a &quot;love detective&quot; movie, the Blue Bird flies back to lead you from surprise to curiosity, to end with an infinite joy after so many thrills to difficulty breathing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Will you follow the student-employee side with tender and unique verses to, or the boss faction with entrepreneural skills? And guess what makes you so touched in life in the middle of Saigon?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s been a long time before the bustling city image in Nguyen Nhat Anh&#39;s work - the unusual appeal of the BlueBird flying back.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&#39;s why the book has only one reading: one circuit from start to finish!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In particular, each book is accompanied by 6 postcards with many paintings by artist Do Hoang Tuong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Author information</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Nguyen Nhat Anh</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nguy&#7877;n Nhat Anh (born May 7, 1955) is a Vietnamese writer. He is best known for his literary works on the subject of his adult life, his works are popular with readers and many have been adapted into films.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In turn, he writes about the stage, is in charge of the sys, is in charge of the children&#39;s page and is now a sports commentator in Saigon Liberation Sunday newspaper under the pseudonym Chu Dinh Ngan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the age of 13, he published his first poem. The first work printed into books was a collection of poems called The City of April (New Works Publishing House, 1984, printed with Le Thi Kim). His first feature-length story was Before the Final Round (Mang Non Publishing House, 1984). Twenty years on, he has focused on writing prose, specializing in youth writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1990, his long story Troubled Boy was awarded the A-list Young Literature Award by the Central Committee of the Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union. , and was voted as one of the 20 typical young writers in 20 years (1975-1995).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1998, he was awarded bestselling books by Kim Dong Publishing House. In 2003, the series of Kaleidoscopes was awarded the Medal for the Young Generation by the Central Committee of the Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union and awarded by the Vietnam Writers&#39; Association. To date, he has published nearly 100 works and has long been a close writer of young readers in Vietnam.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2004, Nhat Anh signed a contract with Kim Dong Publishing House to continue publishing a four-part series titled The Story of Lang Biang about two boys who strayed into the world of witches. This was the first time he had written a series entirely based on imagination. Thus, in preparation for this work, it took him 6 months to study related documents and reading books such as Witches and Wizards, Oriental Legends, Magic and Witchcraft.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After Lang Biang, his next work was the pen of a puppy called I&#39;m Bethles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2008, he released The Give Me a Ticket to Childhood, which was voted the best work of 2008 by The Workers newspaper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2012, Nhat Anh released a long story With two cats sitting by the window. The most recent works were Sitting Crying in a Tree (June 2013), Wishing a Good Day (March 2014), Seven Steps to Summer (March 2015), Con small dogs carrying baskets of roses (February 28, 2016), Young Banana Trees wearing blue shoes (January 7, 2018) and Be friends with the sky (September 2019).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Product prices on Tiki are inclusive of taxes under applicable law. However, depending on the type of product or method, delivery address, additional costs such as shipping fees, bulky cargo surcharges, ...</p>\r\n',
