       (100048, 100001, 'Plague (Nobel Prize in Literature 1957)',
        ',https://salt.tikicdn.com/cache/w444/ts/product/36/48/39/2ef073f6a40a268deb12ecc35a6b1145.jpg', 95600, 150,
        '<p>As soon as it was published in 1947, Albert Camus&#39;s novel Plague made a big impact: 161,000 copies sold out in the first two years. Since then, in the French language alone, this novel has sold over 5 million copies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And after more than 60 years after the author&#39;s death, the world has witnessed real epidemics, such as Ebola, COVID-19, No longer a fictional epidemic, problems related to humanity, how humanity faces the epidemic, a series of meaningful deep layers in the Plague suddenly become understandable , urgent in this day and age. During the plague, Oran, an ugly lifeless city on the algerian coast, had to close itself into a prison because of rats and then one person, two people, tens, hundreds of people died from the plague. Oran turned into a terrible hell, writhing in danger of extinction like many cities before in Europe, Asia, Africa. In the midst of that tragic atmosphere, despite the dangers of infection, the quiet idyllic people, stormed the battle against the Plague.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Strangers, Albert Camus stamped himself on world literature with the absurd human image. And the Plague is where he contemplates human entry as an inevitable path in the search for the meaning of life. Ideology has become symbolic, that symbol is displayed brightly in the dialogues and dialogues of Dr. Rieux. Facing two real beings: physical diseases and soul diseases, Camus&#39;s character finds his human path. And the reader can only be grateful to him for a novel that seems dry under the burden of thought but is clear by the purity of the thought itself, and the quality of love for people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>INTRODUCTION: Albert Camus (1913-1960) was one of the prominent names in French literature in the mid-and-post-World War II decades. Camus&#39; work in the genres of novels, plays, short stories, pens and essays caused heated debate in France and many countries around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Product prices on Tiki are inclusive of taxes under applicable law. However, depending on the type of product or method, delivery address, additional costs such as shipping fees, bulky cargo surcharges, ...</p>\r\n',
