        278900, 120,
        '<p><strong>Crime and Punishment - One of the Greatest Works of All Time (Hardcover) (Re-Published 2020)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Crime and Punishment is the most complete and best novel in the works of the Russian master writer Fyodor Dostoevsky (1821-1881). The story is about the poor student Raxk&ocirc;nnik because he was so lost that he killed two old sisters pawned. In the days that followed, Raxk&ocirc;nnik descended into a new tragedy, severe mental crisis. The more you try to hide your sins, the more embarrassing it becomes. The deep love, the noble sacrifice and the kind heart of the girl Rushedya and the care and love of everyone has awakened Raxk&ocirc;nnik. Ending the inner torn, he makes the decision: it is better to be physically imprisoned than to be spiritually imprisoned.<br />\r\nThe novel is one of the most tragic works of human<br />\r\nliterature. With boundless humanitarian hearts, the author has erected a bleak picture of the deadlocked fate of the russian social bottom class. The work is also a fierce denunciation of the proud 4th class, trampling on morality, dignity and talent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Product prices on Tiki are inclusive of taxes under applicable law. However, depending on the type of product or method, delivery address, additional costs such as shipping fees, bulky cargo surcharges, ...</p>\r\n',
